webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) "The two monkeys who lived at the Museum of Natural History are sitting on a wooden bench in the courtyard. The monkey on the right is a macaque and was named Monjet, now exhibited in the Mammal Hall. : (ev.to postcards): The picture is featured in Gothenburg’s Natural History Annual print 2000. : See also photon. 951-952, 2575, 2973, 3375 and 3079. : Monjet, about 22 years old female died in 1938 (Gen.kat.nr. 1938-7467), lived at the Gothenburg Museum of Natural History for most of his life. It is housed in the Mammalian Hall (25-05-2007) at the Gothenburg Museum of Natural History. Mounted by David Sjölander.' - https://www.europeana.eu/item/52/gnm_photo_GNM2575_001. (en) Leo Bonsdorff. Göteborgs naturhistoriska museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021015942287. CC BY - http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.5/
